vailable-storage":"Available storage, GiB","tooltip_s3-on-prem-configurator_disk-capacity":"Specify the disk size in GiB — this may differ from the marketing GB value. GiB is larger than GB, so the size shown by the operating system will be smaller. For example, a 10 TB disk equals ~9,313 GiB.","tooltip_s3-on-prem-configurator_reserve-percent":"The share of storage used for system operations, defragmentation, and rebalancing on failure. We recommend at least 5%; the smaller the installation, the larger the reserve should be.","tooltip_s3-on-prem-configurator_replication-factor":"Indicates how many times the stored data volume exceeds the volume of a single copy. Redundancy protects against data loss and is implemented through erasure coding and replication.","field_s3-on-prem-metadata-cluster-configurator_objects-count":"Number of objects, million","field_s3-on-prem-metadata-cluster-configurator_rps":"Requests per second","field_s3-on-prem-metadata-cluster-configurator_metadata-nodes-count":"Number of metadata nodes","field_s3-on-prem-metadata-cluster-configurator_metadata-volume":"Net metadata volume, TiB","field_s3-on-prem-metadata-cluster-configurator_disk-size":"Disk size, TiB","tooltip_s3-on-prem-metadata-cluster-configurator_rps":"Average number of requests to stored objects per second. Can be estimated from monitoring data of an existing system, a load forecast, or technical requirements.","tooltip_s3-on-prem-metadata-cluster-configurator_metadata-nodes-count":"Usually 4 nodes are enough, but more may be needed under high memory and CPU load or stricter fault-tolerance requirements."},"error":{"label_description-1":"We are already working on this. Please try ","label_description-2":".","label_description-link":"refreshing the page","label_link-main":"Back to main page","label_meta-title-404":"Page not found | Yandex Cloud","label_meta-title-500":"An error occurred | Yandex Cloud","label_title-404":"Page doesn’t exist","label_title-500":"The server could not l